    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1550</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-04T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 4, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 4—6:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>414. Consulate’s 411, October 3, 2 p.m. A further communiqué was issued last
                    night giving the text of another telegram from the Abyssinian Foreign Minister
                    to the Secretary General. The text reads: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Continuation our previous telegram, four Italian military airplanes this
                            morning bombarded Adowa open town, throwing first bombs on hospital
                            bearing Red Cross emblem. Second bombardment carried out at 10 o’clock
                            by two airplanes. Up to the present time 78 projectiles have been
                            counted.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
